    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.13"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        814 Emerson Avenue, North
                        Minneapolis 11, Minnesota
                        July 23, 1957
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Am wondering whether you got my letter of a few months ago, which, I seem to recall now, was rather lamely facetious, and therefore perhaps not worth answering. But I hope you'll answer this one.</p>
                
                <p>We are moving soon and I want you to know of our whereabouts. We have been to Illinois only once in the last two years. Otherwise I should have tried to see folks, about whom I do think often. I have now finished the course work for the Ph. <hi rend="caps">D.</hi> here at the University of Minnesota. It has dragged along because of the part-time teaching I had to do while studying--and because of my natural intertia, I fear, when it comes to scholarly matters. Now, we must bring in some money again, and so I have taken a teaching position at Eau Claire State College in Wisconsin. We are moving there in two weeks (August 6), and are fortunate to have rented a nice place on Lake Altoona which we look forward to enjoying this coming year. Our new address will be:
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>North Shore Drive</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Lake Altoona</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Eau Claire, Wisconsin</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
                
                <p>Our baby Emily thrives very well. Wish you could see her, for I know you like children at your house. She is seven months old. We are all well.</p>
                
                <p>I've been thinking lately that I might try to do an article on you, Mr. Neihardt, this winter--a kind of appreciation for your achievement. Want to get in touch with you partly for that reason, for I may have to ask some questions.</p>
                
                <p>Kindest thoughts from an old friend.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Bill Lemons</signed>
                </closer>
                    
            </div1>
        </body>
        
